lated to the way the number of virtual impactors\nwithin a time $t_{rel}$ from the first observed close approach accumulates, for\nwhich we prove the existence of a power-law proportional to $t_{rel}^3$. The\npower-law allows us to detect a loss of efficiency in the virtual impactors\nsearch for impact probabilities near the generic completeness limit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 16 Sep 2018 01:41:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Dec 2018 08:28:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 18 Jun 2019 00:12:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-19"}
